An '''AE-35''' was a kind of [[Repulsorlift/Legends|repulsorlift]] unit. The AE-35 required at least six [[rocker-panel cotter pin]]s to operate.

==Behind the scenes==
The [[Star Wars]] AE-35 unit is really an [[Easter egg]], because "AE-35 unit" is the name of the element of the ''Discovery One'' spacecraft that is believed to be malfunctioning in the "Jupiter Mission" segment of [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2001:_A_Space_Odyssey ''2001: A Space Odyssey''].

